ht/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aSemiotics has ever-changing vistas in consonance with changes in the ever-increasing complexity of life on Planet Earth. This book presents cutting-edge work in semiotics, projecting developments in the future of the field. Authored by leading semioticians, Semiotics and its Masters, Volume 2 contains essays on learning, transdisciplinarity, science, scaffolding, narrative, selfhood, ecosemiotics, agency, cybersemiotics, pornography, nostalgia, language and money. The volume presents a panorama of semiotics as it will develop in the third decade of the 21st century. This book will furnish the reader with an overview of the challenges that face explorers in the contemporary world of signs.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aDiskurs. 4aKritik. 4aSemiotics. 4aTransdisziplinarität. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aCritique.  aDiscourse.  aSemiotics.  aTransdisciplinarity.1 aBankov, Kristian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCobley, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEnrique Finol, José, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFavareau, Donald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFontanille, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLandowski, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, Yunhee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeone, Massimo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaran, Timo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeţ, Mariana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aN